The paper presents a novel learning paradigm for feature selection and discovery, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of correlation measures and the focus on identifying groups of informative features suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper's emphasis on improving prediction performance and discovering underlying group structures may also align with sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of real-world datasets and empirical studies may suggest a focus on data analysis and statistics, which could place the paper in sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics).
